==English==

===Etymology===
Origin of the word is subject to much debate but most pundits credit it to ex-player and now manager of [[Crystal Palace F.C.]] [[Iain Dowie]] in reference to his team's unexpected return to winning form. The word was popularised on topical football show Soccer AM on Sky Sports in the United Kingdom, where during the season 2004/05 it has become the object of a cult following.

===Noun===
'''bouncebackability'''

#The ability of a person or team to [[bounce back]], that is, to return to good form after a period of not performing well.
#: ''By passing the test, after last years abysmal failure, he exhibited great '''bouncebackability'''.''

